  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>A woman with straw-colored, flyaway hair and a distant gaze raises her arms and delivers her diatribe to the sky. "I told him! I told that hot-tempered fool to let it go and thank the gods that ogre left our house standing! But no." 

She crosses her arms. It's unclear whether she even sees you. "He went on cursing and blaspheming to anyone who'd listen. And sure enough, the gods sent that beast back to snatch up that ungrateful man."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>"And all the while he hardly took care of the poor pigs! Look at this runt." She finally turns to you, holding an undersized piglet. Its pink snout twitches as it looks at you. 

"I'll bet you could take better care of it than he did!" She shoves it into your arms. Before you can say anything, she turns and flings her hands skyward again, continuing her rant.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>"It's a lesson! Always be thankful for what the gods leave you, no matter how little."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>"...but Rumbald, that hollering fool, where did his fury get him? Into an ogre's belly!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
</StringTableFile>